OLD BUSINESS:
- Discussion regarding a bathroom in Fabick Nature Preserve. During the February 6 Meeting, the Parks and Recreation Committee requested that Staff gather additional information regarding options for a restroom at Fabick Nature Preserve, specifically a cost estimate for a prefabricated structure. 

Due to difficulties obtaining estimates to remodel the existing building, the Board of Aldermen approved going out for formal bids in May. The bid opening occurred on June 15, and although bid packets were requested, no bids were received.

Staff contacted a few of the companies that requested bid packets to inquire as to why they did not bid. Some indicated it was the (small) size of the job and/or a full schedule and others stated that they needed more details in the bid specifications.

Based on the above, Staff is working on a new bid package with revised, detailed specifications and will readvertise the bid opportunity sometime next week. Once the bids are received, they will be forwarded to the Parks and Recreation Committee for review and recommendations to the Board of Aldermen.

- Discussion regarding Municipal Parks Grant Commission Planning Grant. As recommended by the Committee and approved by the Board, Staff has begun applying for the Municipal Park Grant Commission Planning Grant for a Master Plan for the Bud Weil Annex Property.

As a reminder, the application for the grant is revolving throughout the year (no deadline); however, the maximum funding available per project is $10,000, with the City providing a minimum 20% cost-share.

In order to apply for the grant, the City must have selected a planning firm to provide planning services to develop the Master Plan.

Based on the above, a Request For Proposals (RFP) for Park Planning Services was advertised by the City in early May, with a deadline to submit proposals by May 31st. Proposals were received by Gateway Design Studio, LLC, TWM, Inc., Planning Design Studios, and SWT Design and copies of the proposals were provided to the Parks and Recreation Committee in June for review and selection. At that time, the Committee requested additional time to review the proposals and continued the matter to the July Meeting.

At this time, it is requested that the Parks and Recreation Committee, after having reviewed the proposals, assist in selecting a firm for the planning project and make a recommendation to the Board of Aldermen. Please note that selection should be based on the firm that the Committee feels is the best qualified to provide the services. The final cost of the services and scope of work will then be negotiated with the selected firm.

After discussion, Mary Heinemann made a motion to approve selecting Planning Design Studio for the Bud Weil Annex Master Plan under the Municipal Parks Commission Planning Grant, with SWT Design as a backup selection. Mike Abbott seconded the motion.

- 7 Ayes; 0 Nays, 0 Absent, 0 Abstain: Motion APPROVED by voice vote.

